Pia O. wrote a review

PM Pediatrics

I had an extremely frustrating and disappointing experience related to billing after a visit to PM Pediatrics. In December 2024, my child was seen for flu symptoms. The visit involved a standard flu swab and a prescription for Tamiflu. No additional testing was discussed, recommended, or authorized at the time of the visit. Months later, I received a bill from a third-party laboratory (Specialized University Pathologists) for services that were never explained or approved, and my child never visited this practice. When I attempted to resolve the issue, I encountered multiple problems: I was unable to reach anyone for months The laboratory changed their address and phone number after the initial invoice No chain of custody for the specimen could be provided No consent or authorization was on file No documentation linking the test to my child was produced Despite the lack of proof, I was threatened with collections. Ultimately, I paid the bill solely to avoid potential credit damage--not because the charge was valid. What was most disappointing was the lack of support or advocacy from PM Pediatrics in resolving this issue, even though the situation stemmed from care received at their facility. After over a year of effort, I was left with no meaningful assistance. I strongly encourage patients to ask detailed questions about third-party labs and billing practices before agreeing to any testing.

Boban

The wife was feeling like a banh mi sandwich so we decided to try out Boban for dinner. The inside had a clean and modern look to it. The lady working behind the counter was very nice, giving us some recommendations on our 3rd (free) sandwich. After a short wait, our sandwiches and drinks were brought out to us. They were delicious! We will definitely be back when we are craving banh mi or their drinks.

Paired Up

Bought a pair of Travis Scott's black phantoms around October last year. Price was 1,200$, which was whatever understandable they gotta make profit. However months later I wanted to trade it with another couple shoes the verification came back as replicas. Was shocked so I quadruple checked using check check app, numerous stores verified as well. I spoke to Jason the manager via email and he claim he got it from Travis Scott's team, and denied it. Idk if anyone has dealt with getting replicas from this store but make sure you run checks before purchasing. I'll never go back, I received my money back so I'm square but I at least wanted to Inform anyone interested to ensure you verify your shoes before purchasing.
